Heat a splash of @olive oil{} in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Once hot,
quickly brown off the @British beef mince{500%g}, then remove from the pan and
keep to the side.

Peel and chop the @onion{2}(peeled and thinly sliced in half moon shapes).
Heat another splash of @olive oil{} on medium-low heat in your (now empty)
frying pan and cook your onions for around ~{6%minutes}, then add the
@Mexican spice{2%tbsp}.

> Use more or less spice depending on how hot you like it!

Whilst your onion cooks, drain and thoroughly rinse the @red kidney beans{1%400g can}. Mash up the kidney beans in a #bowl{} using a #potato masher{}.

Once your onion has softened, stir in the mashed kidney beans. Add your beef
mince back into the pan. Stir in the @tomato passata{2%cartons} with a pinch of
@salt{pinch} then refill the carton a fifth with water, swirl it around and add
this too.

Pre-heat your #oven{} to 200 degrees. Let the mixture bubble away gently on low
heat until it has thickened up. Meanwhile, roughly chop the @baby gem lettuce{2} and roughly chop the @vine tomatoes{4}.

Once your sauce is thick, take it off the heat. Divide the mixture and spoon it
along one end of each @super soft tortillas with whole wheat{8}. Roll up the
tortillas, place them in a #baking dish{} and grate the @mature cheddar cheese{7%slices} over the top. Cook in your oven until the cheese melts.

Whilst your enchiladas are in the oven, zest the @lime{1}. Mix the
@sour cream{5%tbsp} with a few good grinds of @black pepper{} and your lime zest.

Toss your tomatoes and baby gem in a splash of @olive oil{}, some lime juice, a
pinch of @salt{pinch} and few good grinds of @black pepper{}. Serve your
enchiladas with a dollop of sour cream and your salad on the side. Devour
immediately!